EmmanuelNiyonshuti)\n- Fixed import of ``__main__`` in ``to_process`` workers when entrypoint script\n  doesn't end in ``.py``, such as when using ``console_script`` entrypoints.\n  (`#1027 <https://github.com/agronholm/anyio/issues/1027>`_; PR by @tapetersen)\n- Fixed ``SocketListener.from_socket()`` returning a TCP listener for ``AF_UNIX``\n  listening sockets, causing ``accept()`` to fail with ``ENOTSUP``\n  (`#1132 <https://github.com/agronholm/anyio/issues/1132>`_; PR by @kudato)\n- Fixed ``UDPSocket.aclose()`` and ``ConnectedUDPSocket.aclose()`` on asyncio returning\n  before the underlying socket FD was actually released\n  (`#1147 <https://github.com/agronholm/anyio/pull/1147>`_; PR by @matias-arrelid)\n- Fixed trio backend test runner hanging indefinitely instead of raising an error\nsrc/anyio/__init__.py:73:from ._core._tasks import TaskHandle as TaskHandle\nsrc/anyio/__init__.py:74:from ._core._tasks import create_task_group as create_task_group\ndocs/api.rst:43:.. autofunction:: anyio.create_task_group\ndocs/api.rst:44:.. autoclass:: anyio.TaskHandle\ndocs/tasks.rst:23:    from anyio import sleep, create_task_group, run\ndocs/tasks.rst:33:        async with create_task_group() as tg:\ndocs/tasks.rst:47:As an alternative way to spawn tasks, you can use the :meth:`~.TaskGroup.create_task`\ndocs/tasks.rst:48:method which will return a :class:`~.TaskHandle`. This handle can be used to:\ndocs/tasks.rst:57:    from anyio import TaskHandle, create_task_group, run, sleep\ndocs/tasks.rst:66:        async with create_task_group() as tg:\ndocs/tasks.rst:68:                tg.create_task(sometask(num)) for num in range(5)\ndocs/tasks.rst:77:                if handle.status is TaskHandle.Status.FINISHED\ndocs/tasks.rst:102:        create_task_group,\ndocs/tasks.rst:125:        async with create_task_group() as tg:\ndocs/tasks.rst:155:    from anyio import create_task_group\ndocs/tasks.rst:158:        async with create_task_group() as tg:\ndocs/tasks.rst:171:    from 